Others: Trayce Jackson-Davis is shooting 22 for 27 (77.7%) over the first five games.
Jordan Hawkins played despite earlier back spasms and finished 9 of 21 from the field with four 3-pointers.
Draymond Green had 14 points and six assists.
Andrew Wiggins also sat out consecutive nights because of low back tightness.

Golden State exercised the third-year contract option on second-year guard Brandin Podziemski, who again directed the offense with Curry sidelined and finished with 13 points, nine rebounds and eight assists.
